## Appendix — Exact Commands and Screenshot Checklist

All commands assume the project lives at `D:\koosh\downloads\structural-testing`. JDK 11 is used to avoid class-version mismatches between JaCoCo/ASM (max version 55) and Java 21.

### §1 — One-time environment setup (run once per terminal)

```cmd
set JAVA_HOME=C:\Program Files\Eclipse Adoptium\jdk-11.0.15.10-hotspot
set PATH=%JAVA_HOME%\bin;%PATH%
cd /D D:\koosh\downloads\structural-testing
java -version
```

### §2 — Compile main and test sources

```cmd
del /Q target\classes\*.class target\test-classes\*.class
"%JAVA_HOME%\bin\javac.exe" -d target\classes src\main\java\VendingMachine.java src\main\java\StaticAnalysis.java
"%JAVA_HOME%\bin\javac.exe" -cp target\classes -d target\test-classes src\test\java\VendingMachineTest2.java
```

### §3 — Run tests under the JaCoCo agent (screenshot for Figure 1)

```cmd
del jacoco.exec
java -javaagent:"D:\koosh\downloads\jacoco-0.8.15\lib\jacocoagent.jar"=destfile=jacoco.exec -cp "target\classes;target\test-classes" VendingMachineTest2
```

Take **Figure 1 — Test Execution** (full terminal window including prompt, command, and 14 check-mark / ✗ lines + the `RESULTS: 12 passed, 2 failed` line).

### §4 — Generate the JaCoCo HTML report (screenshot for Figure 2 & Figure 3)

```cmd
rmdir /S /Q jacoco-report
java -jar "D:\koosh\downloads\jacoco-0.8.15\lib\jacococli.jar" report jacoco.exec --classfiles target\classes --sourcefiles src\main\java --html jacoco-report
start "" jacoco-report\index.html
```

Take **Figure 2 — JaCoCo Summary**: the page that opens, showing "Total 54 of 122 55 %" and the per-class table.

Then click the `VendingMachine` class link and take **Figure 3 — VendingMachine Coverage Details** showing lines 12, 14, 16 highlighted in red.

### §5 — Run SpotBugs static analysis (screenshot for Figure 4)

```cmd
"D:\koosh\downloads\spotbugs-4.7.3\bin\spotbugs.bat" -textui -effort:max target\classes
```

Take **Figure 4 — SpotBugs Report**: the terminal showing the four `H B ES:` lines.

